Eight structures were destroyed by the flames and one person is being treated for smoke inhalation. CAPE TOWN - Dozens of people have been displaced following a fire in Cape Town.Eight structures were destroyed by the flames and one person is being treated for smoke inhalation.City of Cape Town fire and rescue service s Theo Lane says: Just after 10pm on Saturday a fire and rescue team responded to an incident in Bonteheuwel. We had eight informal structures destroyed by a fire. The cause of the fire is still unclear.(Edited by Shimoney Regter)